# Documentation Standards

## XML Documentation Requirements
- Include comprehensive XML documentation for all public APIs
- Add `<summary>` tags with clear, concise descriptions
- Document all parameters with `<param>` tags
- Document return values with `<returns>` tags
- Document exceptions with `<exception>` tags

## IntelliSense Optimization
- Write documentation that enhances developer experience
- Use proper cross-references with `<see cref=""/>` tags
- Include `<example>` sections for complex APIs
- Provide meaningful `<remarks>` for additional context
- Use `<value>` tags for properties

## Code Examples
- Include code examples in documentation where helpful
- Use realistic, compilable examples
- Show common usage patterns
- Demonstrate best practices in examples
- Keep examples focused and relevant

## Documentation Quality
- Write clear, professional language
- Avoid redundant or obvious documentation
- Focus on intent and usage rather than implementation
- Update documentation when APIs change
- Review documentation for accuracy and clarity